      %b Ron Derewecki
      earned his Bachelors from West Liberty State College and went on to earn
      a Masters of Education from Penn State University. He taught science in
      the Coshocton school district for over 30 years, including operating the
      planetarium. During his time at Coshocton, he lead many science
      initiatives including: science fairs, summer science camps, and Space
      City (a space camp-like simulation for fourth graders, done on a budget).

  .row.big-up
